<section class="faq-section csv-faq-section" id="faq">
  <div class="container faq-container">
    <h2 class="section-title">Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
    <p class="section-subtitle csv-compact-subtitle">Quick answers about CSV fields, local processing, batch limits, and Pro features.</p>

    <div class="accordion" id="csv-faq-accordion">
      <div class="accordion-item">
        <div class="accordion-header" role="button" tabindex="0" aria-expanded="false">
          <h3>Is this MIDI to CSV converter free?</h3>
          <span class="accordion-icon"><i class="fas fa-chevron-down"></i></span>
        </div>
        <div class="accordion-content">
          <p>Yes. Free tier supports batch conversion up to <strong>20 files / 100MB total</strong>. Pro removes the hard block and adds heavy-batch tools.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="accordion-item">
        <div class="accordion-header" role="button" tabindex="0" aria-expanded="false">
          <h3>Does this converter upload my MIDI files?</h3>
          <span class="accordion-icon"><i class="fas fa-chevron-down"></i></span>
        </div>
        <div class="accordion-content">
          <p>No. Conversion runs <strong>100% locally in your browser</strong>. Your files stay on your device.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="accordion-item">
        <div class="accordion-header" role="button" tabindex="0" aria-expanded="false">
          <h3>What columns are included in the CSV?</h3>
          <span class="accordion-icon"><i class="fas fa-chevron-down"></i></span>
        </div>
        <div class="accordion-content">
          <p><code>track</code>, <code>channel</code>, <code>pitch</code>, <code>note_name</code>, <code>start_seconds</code>, <code>duration_seconds</code>, <code>velocity</code>.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="accordion-item">
        <div class="accordion-header" role="button" tabindex="0" aria-expanded="false">
          <h3>Can I convert multiple MIDI files to CSV at once?</h3>
          <span class="accordion-icon"><i class="fas fa-chevron-down"></i></span>
        </div>
        <div class="accordion-content">
          <p>Yes. Upload multiple files and download results as a ZIP. (Free tier has batch limits; Pro supports larger batches.)</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="accordion-item">
        <div class="accordion-header" role="button" tabindex="0" aria-expanded="false">
          <h3>Why is Pro faster?</h3>
          <span class="accordion-icon"><i class="fas fa-chevron-down"></i></span>
        </div>
        <div class="accordion-content">
          <p>Pro uses <strong>3 concurrent workers</strong> to speed up batch conversion (Free uses 1).</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="accordion-item">
        <div class="accordion-header" role="button" tabindex="0" aria-expanded="false">
          <h3>What is report.json?</h3>
          <span class="accordion-icon"><i class="fas fa-chevron-down"></i></span>
        </div>
        <div class="accordion-content">
          <p>Pro can export a <code>report.json</code> file for batch runs, and ZIP downloads include it automatically. It helps you audit results programmatically.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="accordion-item">
        <div class="accordion-header" role="button" tabindex="0" aria-expanded="false">
          <h3>What if some files fail to convert?</h3>
          <span class="accordion-icon"><i class="fas fa-chevron-down"></i></span>
        </div>
        <div class="accordion-content">
          <p>Pro includes batch retry tools (<strong>Retry all failed</strong> and per-file retry) to recover failed conversions quickly.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="accordion-item">
        <div class="accordion-header" role="button" tabindex="0" aria-expanded="false">
          <h3>Why is track always 1 in my CSV?</h3>
          <span class="accordion-icon"><i class="fas fa-chevron-down"></i></span>
        </div>
        <div class="accordion-content">
          <p>Because many MIDI files are single-track. <code>track</code> refers to MIDI track chunks in the file, not necessarily DAW instrument tracks. Use <code>channel</code> to separate parts.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

